Create an EC-2 ubuntu instance with ports SSH,HTTP,HTTPS and 8080 Custom TCP 
   sudo apt update  (Update your system)
    sudo apt install openjdk-11-jre (Install java 11)
      java -version (To check java version)
      curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee     /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null  
      echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \   https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \ /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null
      sudo apt-get install jenkins   [Install java]
      sudo systemctl enable jenkins [Ebanle Jernkins]
     sudo systemctl start jenkins   [ Start Jenkins]
     sudo systemctl status jenkins  [ To check the status of jenkins]
     Copy the Public IP of our instance and paste in new tab < PUBLIC IP : 8080 >
     cat < Paste the path to get the jenkins password >
     Install all Plugins
     Create Username and Password for Jenkins
     Create a new JOB with free style project pipieline.
     Configure with the GIT-HUB URL from Git-Hub node-to-do repo
     BUILD the pipeline
     cd /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/To-Do-App [ Change into this path ]
     sudo apt install nodejs
     sudo apt install npm
     sudo npm install
     node app.js
     Open the server and in Security Group edit inbound rule and add port number 8000 and save.
     Open the new tab and type < Public Ip : 8080 >  [Now we will able to see the to-do window].
     Now if we refresh the page it will close to fix this follow the below steps: -
      
